We are aware of a behavior that indicates spurious breaker tripped and brownout faults and we are working on some adjustments to make that better. This will not affect the usability of the PDH and fault conditions are not part of the inspection checklist.

@Winston82 , please reach out to us at support@revrobotics.com if you haven’t already. From your picture, it seems like a cluster of four high-current channels are actively faulting, which also sounds like is confirmed by the Hardware Client. This still won’t affect the power distribution capability of the PDH, so you can run it in competition. However, current monitoring is likely not working on those channels.

Again, this isn’t going to affect the power distribution, so we can help you out at your convenience.
